referenceAnswer: Earth materials erode and are carried by flowing water (a river). The earth materials form a delta when the materials are dropped off or deposited when the water stops flowing (at the mouth of a river).

ref_2: Sand gets carried away by the river and settles at the mouth and forms a delta.
